<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-1')">1</a>. I swore it too.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-2')">2</a>. That can't be true. Can it?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-3"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-3')">3</a>. I remember him. He's dead now.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-4"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-4')">4</a>. Now you can see why.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-5"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-5')">5</a>. Calling this Keter truly shows our utter failure of imagination. If this is Keter, how can anything else be? I was there for the debates. Should we create a new class for this? &quot;Apollyon?&quot; Maybe &quot;Prime.&quot; But wait, since we're reliably containing it, maybe it's Euclid, or maybe fucking Safe!</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-6"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-6')">6</a>. Why did this require an O5 vote? Why do we do anything we do?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-7"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-7')">7</a>. We tell ourselves we'll put them back together again, one day when we have the power. We'll bring back every reality ever destroyed, all the casualties along the way&#8230; but how can this be anything but self-justifying moral noise?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-8"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-8')">8</a>. What would a 99% success rate even look like?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-9"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-9')">9</a>. Even you knew this was stupid.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-10"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-10')">10</a>. Oh, yes. A worm is something that flops and dies on the sidewalk when it rains, something to be stepped on with the heel of a boot. A worm is something we can handle. How's this working out? Has it saved a single solitary timeline? Has it even made a single iota of difference?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-11"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-11')">11</a>. Right.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-12"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-12')">12</a>. Or what if we're refueling it by continually attracting it to new timelines? What if the minority reports are correct, and it could have already burned itself out in the vast emptiness between realities?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-13"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-13')">13</a>. You fucking coward.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-14"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-14')">14</a>. Same man who left the note at the end of the Threat's SCP article, by the way.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-15"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-15')">15</a>. How can you possibly confirm something like this?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-16"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-16')">16</a>. Ghoulish. Even though I'm a hypocrite for saying so.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-17"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-17')">17</a>. What if our reality integrity being so low means we were created&#8230; and created badly? How do we know we're the first iteration? How do we even know that some version of us wasn't destroyed already?</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-18"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-18')">18</a>. When you're half-assing the changes, you fuck a timeline up. When you try harder, the timeline improves. Really not that hard to figure it out. And you still think this isn't what it's about? Still think there's nothing out there, watching? The Worm may have no mind, but something out there does. Some<em>things</em>.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-19"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-19')">19</a>. What if we're wrong? What if they're just&#8230; better? What if they deserve to survive, and we don't?</div>
</div>
